## Header Behavior

`headers` and `custom_headers.root` are treated as two inputs for the same effective request headers.

- `headers` accepts `"Name: value"` strings.
- `custom_headers.root` accepts structured key/value entries.
- During planning, apply, and refresh, the provider merges both sources into one canonical header set.
- Order differences returned by the API do not create drift because the provider normalizes the merged values before comparing state.

Example:

```hcl
resource "thousandeyes_http_server" "example" {
  test_name = "Example HTTP Server"
  url       = "https://example.com"
  interval  = 300
  agents    = ["1234"]

  headers = [
    "Content-Type: application/json",
    "X-TE-Test: upgrade-full",
  ]

  custom_headers {
    root = {
      Authorization = "Bearer token"
    }
  }
}
```

The effective header set for this configuration is:

```text
Authorization: Bearer token
Content-Type: application/json
X-TE-Test: upgrade-full
```

